!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

serious /ˈsɪərɪəs/

1. ADJ Serious problems or situations are very bad and cause people to be worried or afraid. 严重的; 危急的 

例： Crime is an increasingly serious problem in Russian society. 犯罪是俄罗斯社会一个日益严重的问题。 

例： The government still face very serious difficulties. 政府仍面临着非常严重的困难。 

2. seriously ADV 严重地; 危急地 

例： If this ban was to come in it would seriously damage my business. 这项禁令如果实施，将会严重地损害我的生意。 

3. ADJ Serious matters are important and deserve careful and thoughtful consideration. 重要的 

例： I regard this as a serious matter. 我认为这是一件重要的事情。 

例： Don't laugh boy. This is serious. 不要笑，伙计。这事很重要。 

4. ADJ When important matters are dealt with in a serious way, they are given careful and thoughtful consideration. 认真的; 严肃的 

例： My parents never really faced up to my drug use in any serious way. 我的父母从未真正认真面对我吸毒的问题。 

例： It was a question which deserved serious consideration. 这是一个值得认真考虑的问题。 

5. seriously ADV 认真地; 严肃地 [ADV with v] 

例： The management will have to think seriously about their positions. 管理层将不得不认真考虑他们的立场。 

6. ADJ Serious music or literature requires concentration to understand or appreciate it. 严肃的 [ADJ n] 

例： ...serious classical music. …严肃的古典音乐。 

7. ADJ If someone is serious about something, they are sincere about what they are saying, doing, or intending to do. 真心的; 郑重的 

例： You really are serious about this, aren't you? 你对这事确实是认真的，是吧？ 

8. seriously ADV 真心地; 郑重地 

例： Are you seriously jealous of Erica? 你真的妒忌埃里卡吗? 

9. ADJ Serious people are thoughtful and quiet, and do not laugh very often. 严肃的 

例： He's quite a serious person. 他是一个相当严肃的人。 

10. seriously ADV 严肃地 [ADV with v] 

例： They spoke to me very seriously but politely. 他们非常严肃但又很有礼貌地与我谈话。

